      "content": "it's just hard to see a version of myself that isn't this. everything i've done for the last half a decade was for this degree. without it, i'm just... empty. and the exhaustion is so deep. it's not even about being sad anymore, it's just this constant, heavy need for everything to just be quiet. for everything to just cease. it feels like the only way to actually get any peace from this pressure is to just stop existing entirely. like, is there even any other way to find that kind of rest?",
